@Node "Introduction" "RxLibnet Introduction"

  @{u}Introduction@{uu}


    This library contains net utility and stack specific functions.

    This library uses rxsocket.library API so it needs rxsocket.library
    installed.

    The environment is macro-private: each macro opens bsdsocket.library
    and what else must be private (e.g. miami.library) and stores a list
    of "things" that must be freed on exit.

    See @{"RxSocket" LINK "rxsocket.guide/main"} documentation for more info.

@EndNode

